<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A <a title="Right-Angle Fold" href="Right-Angle_Fold">right-angle fold</a> made on a <a title="Chopper Folder" href="Chopper_Folder">chopper folder</a>, an <a title="In-Line" href="In-Line">in-line</a> folding device on a <a title="Web Press" href="Web_Press">web press</a>. A chopper fold is commonly the last fold made. Also known as a <a title="quarter fold" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/quarter_fold">quarter fold</a> or <a title="Cross Fold" href="Cross_Fold">cross fold</a>. See <a title="Right-Angle Fold" href="Right-Angle_Fold">Right-Angle Fold</a> and <a title="Chopper Folder" href="Chopper_Folder">Chopper Folder</a>. 
</p>
